â— VERY SIMPLE â€” only one Java file + 2 HTML pages + CSS.

STEP 2: Create pom.xml

Create this file inside BlogWebsiteMaven/

<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 
                             http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    <groupId>com.blog</groupId>
    <artifactId>blogwebsite</artifactId>
    <version>1.0</version>
    <packaging>jar</packaging>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <!-- Plugin to create executable jar -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-jar-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.2.2</version>
                <configuration>
                    <archive>
                        <manifest>
                            <mainClass>App</mainClass>
                        </manifest>
                    </archive>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>


ğŸ‘‰ No dependencies needed
ğŸ‘‰ Maven will simply generate the .jar file

STEP 3: Create App.java

Path:
src/main/java/App.java

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Blog Website Build Successful!");
        System.out.println("Open index.html to view the site.");
    }
}

STEP 4: Create HTML Pages
index.html

Path:
src/main/resources/static/index.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Simple Dynamic Blog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

<h1>Welcome to My Blog</h1>

<p>This is a simple dynamic website using only HTML and CSS.</p>

<a class="btn" href="posts.html">View Blog Posts</a>
<a class="btn" href="submit.html">Write a Blog</a>

</body>
</html>

posts.html

Path:
src/main/resources/static/posts.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Blog Posts</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

<h1>Recent Blog Posts</h1>

<div class="post">
    <h2>Post 1</h2>
    <p>This is a sample blog post. You can add any text here.</p>
</div>

<div class="post">
    <h2>Post 2</h2>
    <p>This is another sample post. Only HTML & CSS used.</p>
</div>

<a class="btn" href="index.html">Back to Home</a>

</body>
</html>

submit.html
src/main/resources/static/submit.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Write a Blog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

<h1>Write a Blog Post</h1>

<form action="submit.html" method="get" class="form-box">
    <label>Title:</label>
    <input type="text" name="title" required>

    <label>Your Blog Content:</label>
    <textarea name="content" rows="6" required></textarea>

    <button class="btn" type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

<p>Your blog will be displayed once backend is added.</p>

<a class="btn" href="index.html">Back to Home</a>

</body>
</html>


style.css

Path:
src/main/resources/static/style.css

body {
    font-family: Arial;
    background: #f2f2f2;
    padding: 20px;
}

h1 {
    color: #333;
}

.btn {
    display: inline-block;
    margin: 10px 0;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    background: #0066ff;
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 5px;
}

.btn:hover {
    background: #0047b3;
}

.post {
    background: white;
    padding: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    border-left: 5px solid #0066ff;
}

.form-box {
    background: white;
    padding: 20px;
    width: 300px;
    border-radius: 5px;
}

input, textarea {
    width: 100%;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    padding: 8px;
}

â­ STEP 5: Install Maven (if not installed)

Download Maven from Google â†’ â€œApache Maven Windowsâ€

Extract zip

Add bin folder to Path

Check version:

mvn -v

â­ STEP 6: Run Maven Commands

Open Command Prompt inside your project folder:

cd BlogWebsiteMaven

Clean build
mvn clean

Compile Java
mvn compile

Package into .jar
mvn package


This will generate:

target/blogwebsite-1.0.jar

â­ STEP 7: Run the JAR (optional)
java -jar target/blogwebsite-1.0.jar


Output:

Blog Website Build Successful!
Open index.html to view the site.

â­ STEP 8: Open Website

Go to:

src/main/resources/static/index.html


Double-click â†’ It opens in browser.

